         <abstract>
            <p>A systematic development of higher order spectral analysis, introduced by Dellwo and Friedman, is undertaken in the framework of an appropriate product space. Accelerated analogues of Osborn's results about spectral approximation are presented. Numerical examples are given by considering an integral operator.</p>
          </abstract>
